########################################################################








this is DISCRETA, a package for the construction 
of combinatorial t-Designs with a prescribed 
automorphism group.

More information can be found on the DISCRETA homepage:
http://www.mathe2.uni-bayreuth.de/~discreta/





REQUIREMENTS:
=============

DISCRETA requires Motif, OpenGL and a C++ compiler.

lesstif may be used as a non commercial substitute for Motif,
Mesa may be used as a non commercial substitute for OpenGL.





INSTALLATION:
=============



1) 
unpack and untar 
discreta.tar.gz
Assume we now have DISCRETA.2000 as a subdirectory 
of your current directory. 

2) 
go into DISCRETA.2000

3) 
edit the file cshrc and adapt to your needs.
In particular, make sure that the variables 

DISCRETA_HOME
MESA_HOME
MOTIF_HOME
DISCRETA_CC
ANSI_CC  

are set properly. 

DISCRETA_HOME should point to the directory DISCRETA.2000

MESA_HOME should point to the directory 
where the libraries and include files of OpenGL (or Mesa) can be found

MOTIF_HOME should point to the directory 
where the libraries and include files of MOTIF (or lesstif) can be found

DISCRETA_CC should be the name of your c++ compiler

ANSI_CC shoul be tha name of your ANSI C-compiler




4)
type
csh


5)
type:
source cshrc

6)
type:
make


7)
put a line 
source ~/DISCRETA.2000/cshrc
into your .cshrc

Modify this line according to the actual place 
of DISCRETA.2000 on your system.
This will allow the system to include the path 
for the discreta executables into its search path.
The path for executables 
is something like
DISCRETA.2000/obj/XXX-YYY-ZZZ/BIN

where XXX, YYY, ZZZ stand for the results of 
uname -s, uname -m, uname -r, respectively.



8)
there is another README in 
DISCRETA.2000/MAIN


